      "copy": {
        "hook": "Nashville Hot Fried Chicken. Two systems — the crust and the glaze.",
        "caption": "The crust is a Wet-Dry-Wet dredging system: a small pour of buttermilk binder worked back into the dry flour creates the craggy surface. The spice paste — cayenne, brown sugar, smoked paprika — is bloomed in hot frying oil after the fry and applied to that surface. The crust earns the glaze. Full recipe at cafeathenathemanual.com. #nashvillehotchicken #cafeathenathemanual #CafeAthenaRecipes",
